Ssyraeth  |  The Venom-Seer  |  Spiders, prophecy, insanity  |  Kethloryn

Lokhruun  |  The Winter Dirge  |  Eternal winter, despair, frozen souls  |  Lokhlannar

Vaelissar  |  The Gilded Rot  |  Beauty, seduction, subtle killing  |  Aelathar, Bressarai

Oczur-Vaal  |  The One Gaze  |  Killing gaze, ocular omens  |  Vaalor

Morkhaz  |  The Red Tempest  |  Berserk rage, joyful slaughter  |  Morkath

Tethzhaar  |  The Iron Serpent  |  Cursed forges, venom-metal  |  Tethrakh

Buaress  |  The Many-Mask  |  Mutation, grafting, body horror  |  Buarath

Firkaan  |  The Shackler King  |  Slavery, broken wills, chains  |  Firvarg

### **Dómnathar Creature Design Principles**

Creatures associated with the Dómnathar should feel: calm, intelligent, patient, inescapable, and morally alien. They are “the absence after the scream.” Their tunnels are resonance-dead corridors that suppress Kin-sense and induce dread and isolation. The Dómnathar Are Horror, Not Action.

### **The Dómnathar Apotheosis Plot (DM-FACING ONLY)**

**DM NOTE:***Apotheosis is morally neutral (Hareem proved it) → requires attunement to all four elements → pure Dómnathar can’t ascend → they need an elementally-attuned being loyal to them. They’ve studied Hareem’s act for 300 years. Candidates: Half-Giants (All-Element Concord, ideal) **>** Half-Dómnathar **>** Silentborn **>** Corrupted Kin.*

### **The Dómnathar Gate Plot (DM-FACING ONLY)**

**DM NOTE:***SEPARATE FROM THE APOTHEOSIS PLOT. The Dómnathar are actively trying to capture or use a high-powered Magi to help start a new gate—a way to reopen a passage to their home world or bring reinforcements. The Magi tradition is the one power system the Dómnathar cannot naturally counter (immune to False Silence), which makes a Magi both their greatest enemy and their most coveted asset. They have spent 300 years quietly targeting and eliminating Magi lineages to reduce the threat, while simultaneously searching for a sufficiently powerful Magi they can control. This is a NEW active plot in the campaign present.*

**DM NOTE:***CRITICAL HIDDEN INFORMATION: There is a SECOND assault gate that the Dómnathar themselves do not know about. This second gate is causing a side effect: the Lord of Stone is comatose. Meanwhile, the Lady of Fire and Lady of Water are actively holding back the Abyss Circle and destroying the first gate.*

## **8. FACTIONS AND FORCES — WHO COMMANDS WHAT**

### **Kin-Aligned Factions**

**Faction**  |  **Alignment**  |  **Role**  |  **Creature Connections**

Golden Roses  |  Varies  |  Hosts the Lament Games. Counter-Deceiver operatives. Branches: Petals (healers), Thorns (warriors), Vines (messengers).  |  Employ/train unusual beasts; track Deceiver creatures

Anacrusis  |  Varies  |  Cross-Kin corruption-hunting scholars. Hierarchy: The Baton → Prime Choirs → Verses/Choruses → Library of Echoes. Trains the Deceiver’s Feat.  |  Study Deceiver creatures

Silent Concord  |  Varies  |  Silentborn ‘third path’ organization. Hierarchy: Stillwater Council → Voice → Choirs (Veil, Hearth, Warden, Memory, Dawn) → Lanterns (cells) → Candles. Trains the Deceiver’s Feat.  |  Lantern cells vs. Dómnathar. Veil Choir: counter-infiltration.

Trade Houses  |  Neutral  |  Merchant organizations  |  Transport exotic beasts; road-side encounters

Chainless Legion  |  Varies  |  Former Firvarg slave-soldiers, settled west of Twin Rivers. Enclaves: Clifftide, Saltrest Haven, Redcurrent Strand.  |  Former war-beasts now independent

Starwind Blades  |  Varies  |  Na’wasua Elf blade-adepts from the Great Forests. Minor faction.  |  Seek cosmic and elemental clues in ancient sites; occasional presence in Kinsweave and desert-edge regions.

Mithril Legion  |  Lawful Good  |  The military brotherhood of the Visetri Dwarves. The oldest active fighting force in Oreka. Organized into shield companies. Well-known player-facing faction. See The Mithril Legion section below.  |  None specific

Steelward Host  |  Lawful Good  |  The defenders of Aldenheim. Extinct — destroyed at the Fall. Mostly forgotten outside scholarly circles. One of the Three Military Orders.  |  None

Stone Covenant  |  Lawful Good  |  Kin-wide standing army headquartered at Kharazhad. Public knows it exists but not its connection to the other two Orders. Full connection revealed only at full membership. Call signs: “We Stand for the Host” / “the stone remembers.”  |  None

### **The Three Military Orders**

The Mithril Legion, the Steelward Host, and the Stone Covenant are the Three Military Orders of Oreka. They share a hidden connection revealed only to full members. The Mithril Legion is well-known and player-facing. The Steelward Host is extinct and mostly forgotten. The Stone Covenant is known to exist but its connection to the other two is not public knowledge.

### **The Mithril Legion**

**[PLAYER-FACING]**

The Mithril Legion is the wandering brotherhood of the Visetri Dwarves — the oldest active fighting force on Oreka and one of the most recognized military organizations in the world. They travel in brightly painted caravans, laugh loudly, trade freely, and are known for their warmth and their fierce loyalty to whoever earns it. Other Kin sometimes mistake them for simple merchants or wandering performers. That mistake is not corrected until it is too late.

The Legion seeks the hottest fights — the battles where others measure the odds and find them wanting. When every other force is calculating retreat the Mithril Legion is already moving forward. They do not negotiate with the present. They advance the moment when the outcome becomes inevitable. They are organized into shield companies. They smile going in.

**[DM-FACING]**

The Visetri solved the problem of having no fortress by becoming one. Every wagon in a Visetri caravan is plated in mithril on the left-facing side. When threatened, the caravans circle. What looked like a traveling caravan an hour ago becomes a mithril-walled fortress that armies have broken themselves against. The transition from traveling to defended takes minutes and has been practiced ten thousand times before any enemy ever tested it.

The Legion’s doctrine has two inseparable halves. The shield companies advance into the hottest fighting, drawing every eye and every weapon. While the enemy is entirely focused on the brotherhood walking toward them, the caravans are circling. By the time the enemy considers retreat the fortress is already behind them. The Legion was never just advancing. They were buying minutes. And the Visetri only need minutes.

The cheerfulness is not a mask. The Visetri have no fortress, no hold, no mountain at their backs. They built their entire civilization on the road, on movement, on the next camp and the next face around the fire. When you live that way the people in front of you right now are everything. You love them loud and bright because tomorrow the road takes you somewhere else. When those people are threatened the smile steps aside — and underneath is a Dwarf. Enduring. Patient. The undeniable future.

The Legion smiles going in because they know what is coming behind them. The caravans circle for the Legion without being asked because the Legion walked forward for them without hesitating. You cannot infiltrate something built on that kind of trust. Nothing is worse than the Legion holding long enough for a Visetri caravan to circle and prepare. The Legion was never the weapon. They were the door closing.

**Connection to the Stone Covenant:** The Covenant is the institution. The Mithril Legion is the spirit the institution was built to honor. The shared name with the Mithril Chains is an intentional red herring — there is no connection between the two.

### **Post-Dark Dawn Evil Factions**

**Faction**  |  **Alignment**  |  **Origin**  |  **Creature Types**

