Bloodridge Coven  |  Chaotic Evil  |  Fleshcrafters, war-witches  |  Mutated creatures, flesh-warped aberrations

Black-Maw Legion  |  Neutral Evil  |  Goblin/warg supremacists  |  Trained wargs, goblin war-machines

The Shrouded Court  |  LN/NE  |  Dómnathar assassin-kings. Trains Deceiver’s Feat.  |  Silence-wielding creatures, shadow beasts

Flamewarg Cults  |  Chaotic Evil  |  Gatefall Remnant descendants; spread westward into the Deepwater Marches over the centuries  |  Fire-infused wargs, flame elementals

### **The Farborn (Gilded Standard Company)**

Neutral Good settled community of ~28,000 near the Lone Titan on the Deepwater Marches’ eastern edge. ~50 pure Titanborne horses, ~900 Titanbreed hybrids. Originally a neutral mercenary outfit from another plane, the Gilded Standard Company was led by Captain Ralven Duskharrow, styled as Duke of the Company. Founded as a Farborn settlement after Duskharrow’s defection during the Running War—only one in ten of the original Company survived. The Farborn are isolated at the Titan and interact with Kin primarily during trade meets. Three centuries of fair dealing have built trust. They register as No Registration on Kin-sense—invisible—but this has not prevented a functional relationship. The Farborn are tentatively, slowly becoming a fifth human kin.

**Titanbreed Horse Pricing:** Titanbreed hybrid cavalry mounts command 8,000–15,000 gp depending on training, bloodline proximity, and temperament. Titanborne purebloods (~50 in existence) are never sold—they are sacred to the Farborn and serve as breeding stock and ceremonial mounts only.

*Other mentioned breakaway factions (Ashen Menders, Ember-Slack Goblins, Free-Banner Ogres, Veil-Orphans, Sundered Hand) need further development.*

## **9. CREATURE CATEGORIES — THE THREE-TIER BESTIARY SYSTEM**

**Tier 1: Oreka Originals**

Creatures invented specifically for Oreka, born from its elemental forces, history, and cultures. Most detailed lore, cultural significance, and regional placement.

**Tier 2: Mythological Adaptations**

Creatures drawn from global mythology (Persian, Slavic, Japanese, African, Polynesian, Norse, Celtic, Greek, Mesoamerican, and more), adapted to Oreka’s framework.

**Tier 3: OGL Creatures (3.5e Adapted)**

Standard SRD/OGL creatures given Oreka-specific context. Must have Kin-Sense Signature, Elemental Affinity, Regional Placement, and Cultural Significance.

## **10. OREKA-SPECIFIC DESIGN FIELDS**

**Field**  |  **Required?**  |  **Description**

Kin-Sense Signature  |  REQUIRED  |  Category (Harmonic, Wild Static, Breach Static, Warm Static, Null, Void, None, Raw Static) plus descriptive sensory text.

Elemental Affinity  |  REQUIRED  |  Primary/secondary attunement. Dómnathar: “None — Extraplanar.”

Cultural Significance  |  REQUIRED  |  How specific Kin cultures relate to this creature.

Regional Placement  |  REQUIRED  |  Which of the Seven Regions; population density and habitat.

Lore (Knowledge Check)  |  Recommended  |  Tiered DC 10/15/20/25/30 results per MM III format.

Strategies and Tactics  |  Recommended  |  Combat behavior, preferred terrain, group tactics.

Faction Alignment  |  If applicable  |  Which faction(s) the creature serves.

Historical Origin  |  If applicable  |  Which event created or introduced it.

